Package edu.cmu.tetrad.graph

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Graph
    Implements a graph capable of storing edges of type N1 *-# N2 where * and # are endpoints of type Endpoint.
    GraphConstraint
    An interface representing a syntactic constraint that certain graphs need to obey when adding or removing nodes or edges.
    GraphGroup
    I couldn't find a mechanism in place to manage algorithms that return potentially more than 1 graph.
    Node
    Represents an object with a name, node type, and position that can serve as a node in a graph.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AtMostOneEdgePerPair
    A graph constraint prohibitting more than one edge per node pair from being added to the graph.
    Dag
    Represents a directed acyclic graph--that is, a graph containing only directed edges, with no cycles.
    DirectedEdgesOnly
    A graph constraint permitting only directed edges to be added to the graph.
    DirectedUndirectedOnly
    A graph constraint permitting only directed or undirected edges to be added to a graph.
    Edge
    Represents an edge node1 *-# node2 where * and # are endpoints of type Endpoint--that is, Endpoint.TAIL, Endpoint.ARROW, or Endpoint.CIRCLE.
    EdgeListGraph
    Stores a graph a list of lists of edges adjacent to each node in the graph, with an additional list storing all of the edges in the graph.
    EdgeListGraphSingleConnections
    Stores a graph a list of lists of edges adjacent to each node in the graph, with an additional list storing all of the edges in the graph.
    Edges
    This factory class produces edges of the types commonly used for Tetrad-style graphs.
    Endpoint
    A typesafe enumeration of the types of endpoints that are permitted in Tetrad-style graphs: null (-), arrow (->), and circle (-o).
    EndpointMatrixGraph
    Stores a graph a list of lists of edges adjacent to each node in the graph, with an additional list storing all of the edges in the graph.
    FruchtermanReingoldLayout
    Lays out a graph by linearly summing repulsive force between all nodes and attractive force between adjacent nodes.
    GraphConverter
    Converts graphs used in the search package from one type to another.
    GraphGeneratorRandomNumEdges
    Modifies the UniformGraphGenerator to generate random DAGs (not assuming connectivity) with number of edges in given range, min to max.
    GraphNode
    Implements a basic node in a graph--that is, a node that is not itself a variable.
    GraphUtils
    Basic graph utilities.
    GraphUtils.GraphComparison  
    GraphUtils.TwoCycleErrors  
    InArrowImpliesNonancestor
    A graph constraint that checks to make sure that in-arrows imply non-ancestry-- that is, when adding an edge A *--> B, where * is any endpoint, B is not an ancestor of A.
    IndependenceFact
    Stores a triple (x, y, z) of nodes.
    KamadaKawaiLayout
    Lays out a graph by placing springs between the nodes and letting the system settle (one node at a time).
    LagGraph
    Implements a graph allowing nodes in the getModel time lag to have parents taken from previous time lags.
    LayeredDrawing
    Lays out a graph by placing springs between the nodes and letting the system settle (one node at a time).
    MeasuredLatentOnly
    This graph constraint permitting only measured or latent nodes to be added to the graph.
    MisclassificationUtils
    Some utilities for generating misclassification tables for graphs.
    NodeEqualityMode
    Sets whether nodes are compared by the equals method or by object identity.
    NodePair
    An unordered pair of nodes.
    NodeType
    A typesafe enum of the types of the types of nodes in a graph (MEASURED, LATENT, ERROR).
    NoEdgesToSelf
    A graph constraint prohibitting edges being added to a graph which connects any given node to itself.
    OrderedPair<E>
    An ordered pair of objects.
    Pattern
    To see what Pattern is, look at the graph constraints it uses.
    SemGraph
    Represents the graphical structure of a structural equation model.
    TimeLagGraph
    Represents a time series graph--that is, a graph with a fixed number S of lags, with edges into initial lags only--that is, into nodes in the first R lags, for some R.
    TimeLagGraph.NodeId  
    Triple
    Stores a triple (x, y, z) of nodes.
    UniformGraphGenerator
    Generates random DAGs uniformly with certain classes of DAGs using variants of Markov chain algorithms by Malancon, Dutour, and Philippe.
